oduce an interacting binary with the BH, or a\nnon-interacting, hard binary; both could be candidates of BH high- and low-mass\nX-ray binaries. Hence our simulations especially confirm that strong encounters\ncan lead to the formation of the (generally difficult to form) BH low-mass\nX-ray binaries.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Nov 2022 20:18:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 Jan 2023 06:12:34 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 5 Jan 2023 20:09:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-18"}
